toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>614</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00U0</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00U0.xml</fr:route><fr:title>New <fr:code>forester init</fr:code> command</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>4</fr:month><fr:day>15</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="kentookura.xml"
type="local"
addr="kentookura">Kento Okura</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00S9</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>To make it easier to set up a new forest, we have added a <fr:code>forester init</fr:code> command; when you run this command in an empty directory, it will initialise a git repository with a submodule for the <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-base-theme"
type="external">default theme</fr:link> pinned to the correct release, and a <fr:link
href="jms-00RG.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00RG">configuration file</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>617</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00SP</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00SP.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Changed behaviour of queries</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>4</fr:month><fr:day>15</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00S9</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Forester’s <fr:link
href="jms-0066.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-0066">rudimentary support for queries</fr:link> has been simplified somewhat. Previously, the results of a query would be gathered and, if non-empty, placed underneath an anonymous subtree (whose title could be modified using <fr:link
href="jms-0067.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-0067">transclusion options</fr:link>).</fr:p><fr:p>In light of the <fr:link
href="jms-00O4.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00O4">user-level support for anonymous subtrees</fr:link> introduced in <fr:link
href="jms-00HY.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00HY">Forester 3.1</fr:link>, the behaviour of queries has been simplified: the results of a query are simply transcluded directly without being enclosed in a subtree.</fr:p><fr:p>Although the new beahviour is simpler, it is no longer possible to have a query subtree that is hidden when it returns no results. Users should treat the querying feature as highly provisional, and subject to change and even potential removal.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>619</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00SQ</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00SQ.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Addresses for anonymous trees</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>4</fr:month><fr:day>15</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00S9</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Previously, a subtree could be emitted without any address; this greatly complicated the logic of the graph analysis, <fr:link
href="jms-00O3.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00O3">designated parents</fr:link>, and other things. Now, emitting an anonymous subtree generates a fresh address in a separate namespace; as a result, these trees get rendered to their own XML file. Naturally, an anonymous subtree cannot be linked to or transcluded, but it can now participate properly in the graph analysis.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>621</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00SA</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00SA.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Incremental parsing</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>4</fr:month><fr:day>15</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="nickhu.xml"
type="local"
addr="nickhu">Nick Hu</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00S9</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Menhir’s incremental parsing API is adopted in order to make the parser more resiliant to syntax errors. The goal is to support language server protocol diagnostics in a future release.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
